weatherboard
Homonym Number:
Word Class:noun
Sense Number:3
Definition:a thin plank of wood used in overlapping rows to cover the outside of a house.
Origin:
Register:
Register 2:
Domain:[none]
Region:[none]
See:
Pronunciation:
Notes: [p.211 1971 Smithyman fn 11. Weatherboard. Although originally metropolitan, in the nineteenth century this seems to have become predominantly colonial, of boards laid horizontally, nailed with overlapping edges. Examples in the <i>Oxford English Dictionary</i> are almost wholly Australian.
